    "body": "@ajaxboy Please direct questions / code help request to the community discussion forums or to slack.  The github issues section is intended to be only used for bugs with Electron.\n\nI'll answer your question anyway though ðŸ‘ \n\nTo check if a file exists you want to use [`fs.stat`](https://nodejs.org/api/fs.html#fs_fs_stat_path_callback)\n\nSample code would be\n\n``` js\nconst pathToFile = '/path/to/my/file';\nfs.stat((err) => {\n  if (err) {\n    // File does not exist\n  } else {\n    // File does exist\n  }\n});\n```\n\nAnd before anyone else says \"you should use fs.exists\", that method is deprecated so using it is a super bad idea.\n"
